00:01:47.333 --> 00:01:48.600
SAM KILLERMAN: We might as well.

00:01:48.600 --> 00:01:50.367
SAM KILLERMAN: Let's
just go right there.

00:01:50.367 --> 00:01:51.867
SAM KILLERMAN: If you haven't
already talked about penises

00:01:51.867 --> 00:01:53.834
and vaginas, we need to talk
about penises and vagina,

00:01:53.834 --> 00:01:55.400
because that's what
everybody always thinks.

00:01:55.400 --> 00:01:57.367
Immediately, as soon
as you say gender,

00:01:57.367 --> 00:01:59.166
anybody who's walking by
right now who's hearing us

00:01:59.166 --> 00:02:00.667
say the word "gender,"
the first thing

00:02:00.667 --> 00:02:02.300
that's popping to their
mind is external genitalia.

00:02:02.300 --> 00:02:03.867
They're thinking about
penises and vagina.

00:02:03.867 --> 00:02:06.633
KATIE COURIC: So for the
purpose of our discussion,

00:02:06.633 --> 00:02:08.934
the bottom line is,
your external genitalia

00:02:08.934 --> 00:02:10.400
